          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Date ticklabels often overlap, so it is useful to rotate them and right align them.  Also, a common use case is a number of subplots with shared x-axis where the x-axis is date data.  The ticklabels are often long, and it helps to rotate them on the bottom subplot and turn them off on other subplots, as well as turn off xlabels."
